etymologies: late Middle English (as a noun denoting a set of four): from Latin quaternarius, from quaterni ‘four at once’, from quater ‘four times’, from quattuor ‘four’

definitions: fourth in order or rank; belonging to the fourth order.
relating to or denoting the most recent period in the Cenozoic era, following the Tertiary period and comprising the Pleistocene and Holocene epochs (and thus including the present).
shortDefinitions: of most recent period in Cenozoic era

definitions: denoting an ammonium compound containing a cation of the form NR₄⁺, where R represents organic groups or atoms other than hydrogen.
shortDefinitions: denoting ammonium compound containing cation of form NR ₄

definitions: (of a carbon atom) bonded to four other carbon atoms.
shortDefinitions: (of carbon atom) bonded to four other carbon atoms

definitions: the Quaternary period or the system of deposits laid down during it.

notes.text: The Quaternary began about 1,640,000 years ago. Humans and other mammals evolved into their present forms and were strongly affected by the ice ages of the Pleistocene

shortDefinitions: Quaternary period or system of deposits laid down during it
